Title: The Financing and Redeployment of Specific Assets 
Abstract:
 We model the role various forms of nonrecourse secured debt play in
 efficiently redeploying assets whose value is state-specific. Ex ante, an
 entrepreneur and an asset redeployer make noncontractible state-specific
 investments in the primary and next-best uses of an asset, respectively.
 The redeployer provides a secured nonrecourse loan equal to the value of
 the asset in the critical state that separates the good and bad states. In
 the event of a bad state, this contract averts ex post bargaining over the
 asset's quasi-rents on redeployment and leaves the parties' ex ante
 investments undistorted. Copyright The American Finance Association 1999. 
