Author-Workplace-Name: Department of Economics, Faculty of Business Administration, Simon Fraser University 
Title: On the Cross-Sectional Relation between Expected Returns, Betas, and Size 
Abstract:
 In this paper, I set up scenarios where the mean-variance capital asset
 pricing model is true and where it is false. Then I investigate whether
 the coefficients from regressions of population expected excess returns on
 population betas, and expected excess returns on betas and size, allow us
 to distinguish between the scenarios. I show that the coefficients from
 either ordinary least squares or generalized least squares regressions do
 not allow us to tell whether the model is true or false. Copyright The American Finance Association 1999. 
